page.title: 14The wildlife of our 'D'block
page.content: The wildlife in our area is mainly birds{e.g.sparrows,thrushes,starlings {,blackbirds,crows,blue and great tits {,rooks,magpies,sea gulls,green,gold, {bull and chaffinches We do have some{rabbits,squirrels, {hedgehogs}and the occassional{fox.} We also have a local{kestrel,}which has its nest just outside our school. The kestrel would hover way up in the sky and suddenly dive down to the ground,it might have spotted a small {rodent.}If the kestrel flys back up into the air and starts hovering again ,it means it has missed its prey,but if it stays down on the ground for a few seconds and then flys off,it means it has caught its prey and eaten it or taken it back to feed its{chicks. You would think that the M25 would scare off all wildlife,but infact the enbankments are filled with mice.
